Re: Vesicular stomatitis, equine - USA (09): (TX) bovine, more cases 20140731.2648461
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VSV [vesicular stomatitis virus] research to date has not identified a viremic stage in mammals, so the moderator's hypothesis that "VS virus is circulating in the white tail deer population in that area" is not supported by current research. As of yet, VSV research has not been able to identify a mammalian reservoir for the virus, although the search for a possible reservoir continues. Transmission has been demonstrated by infected biting fly vectors (black flies, sand flies, culicoides, and/or other known vectors); transmission via these vectors is ongoing.

For current weekly situation reports and maps depicting all confirmed cases of VSV in the U.S. this outbreak season (both Texas and Colorado are currently affected states), please see the regularly updated VSV page of the USDA-APHIS website: http://www.aphis.usda.gov/wps/portal/aphis/ourfocus/animalhealth?1dmy&urile=wcm%3apath%3a%2Faphis_content_library%2Fsa_our_focus%2Fsa_animal_health%2Fsa_animal_disease_information%2Fsa_equine_health%2Fsa_vesicular_stomatitis%2Fct_vesicular_stomatitis.

