[Many thanks for the correction when I trailed my coat. But noting the universal difficulty of demonstrating any VS viraemias, I would expect, unless it has been demonstrated that white tail deer are resistant to experimental VS infection, that the deer in this latter area (Kinney and Val Verde counties) of west Texas, which is dense with ranched deer, are being exposed. The ranchers there are reluctant to report problems as it can affect their profit in the upcoming hunting season. But it would not be the 1st time I was incorrect.

I recommend that subscribers visit the admirable USDA-APHIS VSV site. - Mod.MHJ

